-- Impala Platinum, Nedbank, Sappi May Move: South African Equity Preview
-- Mike Cohen
-- 2010-08-01T11:03:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-01/impala-nedbank-kumba-sappi-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  
 The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  dropped 194.86, or 0.7
percent, to 28,355.21 in Johannesburg.  
 Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd.  (IMP SJ): The world’s second-
largest platinum producer resumes talks aimed at resolving a
wage dispute with the South Africa’s National Union of
Mineworkers. The shares rose 46 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 197.49
rand.  
 Nedbank Group Ltd.  (NED SJ): South Africa’s fourth-biggest
bank releases first-half earnings. The shares fell 90 cents, or
0.7 percent, to 135.21 rand.  
 Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.  (KIO SJ): South Africa’s government may
announce a decision on disputed prospecting rights at Sishen,
Africa’s largest iron ore mine. Kumba is challenging the
decision to award 21.4 percent of the rights at Sishen to
Imperial Crown Trading Ltd., a company whose only asset is that
right. Kumba owns the rest of the mine’s rights. Kumba’s shares
rose 3 rand, or 0.8 percent, to 370 rand.  
 Sappi Ltd.  (SAP SJ): The world’s largest producer of glossy
magazine paper reports fiscal third-quarter earnings. The stock
fell 15 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 35.05 rand.  
 The following shares begin trading without the right to
their latest dividend:  
 Brait SA (BAT SJ), Illovo Sugar Ltd. (ILV SJ), SABMiller
Plc (SAB SJ).  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) added 0.7 percent to $19.80.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 2.4 percent to $40.52. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) fell 0.2 percent to $61.54. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) rose 2 percent to $4.14. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI US)
rose 3.7 percent to $13.53. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY US)
advanced 2.7 percent to $10. Impala Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US)
climbed 1.1 percent to $26.84. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) rose 1.5
percent to $4.79. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) fell 0.1 percent to
$39.64.  
